text.tspan: Josiah McMenamy
Dear Hiring Manager,
I have a deep interest in accomplishing complex tasks with software to create something
that can have a significant impact.
My most recent experience was at FreeWheel, a Comcast company, where I greatly
enjoyed learning new things and challenging myself. I created a novel service to capture
cost metric KPIs for the Userdata team, which analyzes $3M in annual spend. In order to
create the service, I had to use technologies such as Snowflake, AWS Services
(CloudWatch, S3, ECR, EKS), ArgoCD, Kubernetes, and Docker. I collaborated with the
SRE team and created an observability dashboard on Grafana cloud utilizing a
Prometheus push gateway. Aside from this larger project, I spent some time refactoring
AWS Lambda code with the factory design pattern and contributed to an internal metric
library, both of which are being adapted into production projects. This experience made
me very comfortable with accepting limited project guidance and designing the best
solution I could come up with.
I have also worked as a software engineer intern for Cisco systems, specifically their San
Jose and London WebEx teams. This role gave me great experience working in a Jira
driven environment, contributing and collaborating with others in the group. I spent my
time enhancing their internal diagnostic tool ‘Call Tracker’ by fixing bugs and
completing feature requests. One large project I undertook was moving Call Tracker from
Bootstrap 3 to Bootstrap 4 as well as using new features of Bootstrap to stylize the
webpage. My work allowed me to learn about front end development with Java and
AJAX, while also incorporating some back end development with Python. I believe the
highly varied nature of my work will be easily applied to this position because I gained a
wide breadth of knowledge in Software Engineering.
Thank you for considering me for this position.
Best Regards,
Josiah McMenamy
